  "text": "Previous studies demonstrated that ROS induction activates the ERK pathway [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Western blot analysis showed that apocynin significantly inhibited UA-induced ERK1/2 phosphorylation simultaneously (Fig. 11A) . Apocynin suppressed the expression of cyclin D1 and cyclin A2 (Fig. 11, B and C) . ]thymidine incorporation and cell counting showed that apocynin inhibited UA-induced cell proliferation (Fig. 11, D and E) . Thus UA stimulates rat MC proliferation partially by increasing the expression of cyclins by activation of the ERK pathway via NADPH oxidase-derived ROS generation.",
